snippet.textDisplay: My mom always drew inspiration from real people, things and stories. This reminded me of one of those bed time stories that she used to whisper while I'd try to fall asleep. This one story was about a small town girl who aspired to be so many things but she couldn't due to lack of resource and limited exposure. She goes on to find a lot of peace and happiness when his prince charming comes along one day almost to sound like he rescued her. They moved on in life together to settle at this almost utopian riverside town. The news of her expected first baby girl-lifted her spirits as she could finally see her daughter living the dream and be whoever she wants, that may be she couldn't be. She used to end the story here telling me that it is time for me to sleep. Years later, I went on to discover that the girl in the story was my mom and the baby girl she spoke of fondly couldn't survive the birth. She lost her first born. This song made me realise how some losses can never be forgotten.
